Package ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.caclulator.complex

Record Class Complex

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.caclulator.complex.Complex
public record Complex(double r, double i) extends Record
The Complex record obviously represents a complex number, which is defined as an element of a number system that extends the real numbers with a specific element denoted i, called the imaginary unit and satisfying the equation i^2 = -1; every complex number can be expressed in the form a+bi, where a, b âˆˆ R.

This implementation allows to perform some basic algebraical operations, namely add(Complex), substract(Complex), multiply(Complex), divide(Complex) and negate(). Such trigonometric functions as sin() and cos() are also provided.

toString() represents an instance of this record as a string in format a+bi, where a is a real part of this complex number and b is an imaginary one.

Complex number can be initialized by the default auto-generated Complex(double, double) constructor or valueOf(String) method, which argument has to represent an instance of this record the same way as it is done by toString().
